derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: from late Latin incompletus, from Latin in- 'not' + completus 'filled, finished' (see complete)

entry.def: Something that is incomplete is not yet finished, or does not have all the parts or details that it needs.

example.ex: The clearing of rubbish and drains is still incomplete...

example.ex: European political union would be incomplete without a defence element...
